
[1]deviate

   DEVIATE, v.i. [L., way.]

   1. To turn aside or wander from the common or right way, course or
   line, either in a literal or figurative sense; as, to deviate from the
   common track or path, or from a true course.

   There nature deviates, and here wanders will.

   2. To stray from the path of duty; to wander, in a moral sense; to err;
   to sin.
